# Handoff Workflow

Always read `HANDOFF.md` before starting meaningful work in this repository.

Use `HANDOFF.md` to understand:
- what the project is
- current status
- what changed last
- files recently touched
- open issues
- next best step
- guardrails and known decisions

Before ending a meaningful work session, update `HANDOFF.md` to reflect the current state of the project.

When updating `HANDOFF.md`, keep it short, current, and practical. Update these sections when relevant:
- Current Status
- Last Session Changes
- Files Touched
- Open Issues
- Next Best Step
- Known Decisions

Do not turn `HANDOFF.md` into a long diary or changelog.
Do not duplicate the README.
Prefer concise bullet points over long paragraphs.

When in doubt:
- preserve working logic
- avoid unnecessary rewrites
- follow the Next Best Step unless a blocker requires otherwise